# Autocur: Db2ConnectionTest

## Purpose
Run DB2 connection test to FKMTST using DedgeCommon. Verifies connection only (no MCP pipeline).

## Deploy
1. Publish Db2ConnectionTest: `dotnet publish Db2ConnectionTest -c Release -o Db2ConnectionTest`
2. Run `Db2ConnectionTest\_deploy.ps1` to deploy to dedge-server

## Trigger
```powershell
. "C:\opt\src\DedgePsh\DevTools\CodingTools\Cursor-ServerOrchestrator\_helpers\_CursorAgent.ps1"
Invoke-ServerCommand -Command '%OptPath%\DedgePshApps\Db2ConnectionTest\Run-TestDb2Connection.ps1' -ServerName 'dedge-server'
```

## Log Path
- Central: `C:\opt\src\DedgeSrc\DedgeSystemTools\Folders\Opt\data\AllPwshLog\FkLog_YYYYMMDD.log`
- Or app-specific if Set-OverrideAppDataFolder: `C:\opt\src\DedgeSrc\DedgeSystemTools\Folders\Opt\data\Db2ConnectionTest\FkLog_YYYYMMDD.log`
- Copy locally before reading (per autocur rule)

## Success Pattern
- `JOB_COMPLETED`
- `DB2 connection OK: Server=..., User=...`
- `finished with exit code: 0`

## Failure Pattern
- `JOB_FAILED`
- `|ERROR|`
- `finished with exit code: 1`

## Pre-deploy
Before deploy, build and publish Db2ConnectionTest exe into the folder that gets deployed.
